headline.main: U.S. BATAAN FLIERS PICK OFF THEIR FOE; Two of MacArthur's Fighter Pilots Meet Three Japanese, Bag Them One by One ENEMY GROWING CAUTIOUS Americans With Relatively Few Planes Use Air Skill to Battle Without Losing Any

lead_paragraph: WITH THE UNITED STATES FORCES ON BATAAN PENINSULA, Jan. 29 (Delayed) -- American fighting planes and pilots remaining in this area may be few, but they still pack a wallop.
abstract: U S pilots without planes volunteer for land fighting
